tspan.tspan: Milton Madison was born and raised in
Birmingham, Alabama. His love of comic books
and Lowrider magazines would help nurture
his passion for drawing until college. After
with a degree in graphic arts and design, he
then pursued painting. His works have been
featured at the National Center for the Study
of Civil Rights and African-American Culture,
the Birmingham Public Library and The Rosa
Parks Museum. Along with Sunny Paulk,
Milton designed and painted hid first mural @

text.tspan: Thats My Child TMC where he also taught art.
